a = (7, 14, 0, 21, 28, 0, 35, 42, 0, 49) # This line creates a tuple 'a' with the values 7, 14, 0, 21, 28, 0, 35, 42, 0, and 49. The tuple contains a mix of integers and zeros.
print(a) # This line prints the tuple 'a', which will output (7, 14, 0, 21, 28, 0, 35, 42, 0, 49).
n = a.count(0) # This line counts the number of occurrences of the value 0 in the tuple 'a' using the count() method. The output will be 3, as there are three zeros in the tuple.
print(n) # This line prints the value of 'n', which will output 3.
